	    <tr>
         <td style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 10pt;" background="/images/bg_heading_green_01.jpg"><center><b>Looking to start a new guild</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		 <td>                            
	                                   

	    <table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
		  <tr><td><font color="00dd00">Submitted by:</td><td><font color="00dd00">Markax</td></tr>
        </table>
	  <br>
	  <br>


          I am hoping to start a new guild but am having a bit of trouble getting people in game (I'm kind of isolate in Kunark), also, the idea behind the guild is not entirely popular, but here the general premise.<br>
          <br>
          The Natural Order<br>
          <br>
          1) The guild is meant as a non-twink guild.  Members should have gear appropriate to their level and/or have made the gear themselves.<br>
          <br>
          2) If you want an item, work WITH fellow guild members to get such items.  Basically, if you want the item, you're going to have to put the work in to get it.<br>
          <br>
          3) Group with other guild members whenever possible.  Arrange times you will meet and where you will hunt.  This would be in a raid-like style, but would not have to include large numbers of the guild members, just say 3 to 6 people.  This should build a cohesiveness among guild members and prepare us for encounters in the future where grouping is a necessity.<br>
          <br>
          4) Camp spawns for experience, not for items.  If a spawn drops an item you could use (particularly your guild character) AND you can get experience from killing it, go for it.  If it's a spawn that you don't get experience from, get your item and leave and let others that can get experience move in.<br>
          <br>
          5) Be respectful of others, all others, not just those in the guild.<br>
          <br>
          I don't see this as ever being an uber-guild (and honestly I'd rather it not become one), nor do I see it having a huge population.  I think 20 or so members would be a great size.  Not too small that raids and such later in EQ life would not be too difficult, nor too large that noone in the guild knows anyone else.<br>
          <br>
          If you're interested in such a guild, send me (Markax), Sharkorr or Valkre a tell in game or send me an e-mail at pklafta@kscable.com.  Once we have the number of people needed to start the guild, we'll build it from there.<br>

          </td>
		 </tr>
